In July last year, another Egyptian journalist who had worked for Al Jazeera, Mohamed Monir, 65, died of the novel coronavirus, his daughter said, days after he was released from detention on charges of "membership of a terrorist group, dissemination of false news and improper use of social networks".
Since President Abdel Fattah al-Sisi took office in 2014, his government has cracked down heavily on any display of dissent.
Those suspected of supporting the government of former Islamist president Mohamed Morsi, whose ouster Sisi led as army chief in 2013, have been particular targets. Basma Mostafa was brought before prosecutors on Sunday after going missing the day before while reporting on unrest in Al-Awamya. Interior ministry claims state news agency Anadolu is a front for a troll farm. A total of 13 independent aspirants have expressed interest to contest in the Nairobi by-election. Majimbo Simiyu Kalasinga bagged the Ford Kenya party ticket by beating Nakuru East Sub-county Commissioner Erick Wanyonyi 75 to 30 votes. Senate Majority Chief Whip says he did not give the letter to any media outlet.